<p>Springfield's Cold-Mixed climate zone requires HVAC systems capable of handling temperature extremes, from summer highs in the 90s to winter lows below freezing. For optimal efficiency, homeowners should consider heat pumps with SEER ratings of 16-18 for cooling and HSPF ratings of 9-10 for heating. Dual-fuel systems combining heat pumps with gas furnace backup work exceptionally well in Springfield, providing efficient heat pump operation during mild weather and reliable gas heating during extreme cold snaps when heat pump efficiency drops.</p>

