<p>Missouri offers additional state-level support through net metering policies that allow solar customers to receive credit for excess electricity fed back into the grid. City Utilities participates in net metering programs, crediting customers at retail rates for solar production. While City Utilities doesn't currently offer specific solar rebates, they do provide energy efficiency rebates for high-efficiency HVAC systems, heat pumps, and smart thermostats. These rebates can range from \$200-800 depending on the efficiency rating and type of equipment installed. Additionally, Missouri's property tax exemption for solar installations ensures that adding solar panels won't increase property tax assessments.</p>

