<p>Newer developments like Southgate and areas around South Springfield offer excellent solar potential with fewer shading obstacles and modern electrical systems that integrate easily with solar installations. The Sequiota and Galloway neighborhoods, with their mix of home sizes and ages, represent typical Springfield solar opportunities where 6-8kW systems match well with average energy consumption patterns. For homes near Missouri State University and in the Midtown area, smaller solar systems may be appropriate due to generally smaller home sizes, while the energy savings from City Utilities' 11.2¬¢/kWh rate still provide attractive returns on investment.</p>

